		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">renegade74 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">c+) or, write an importer program that recognizes tiles from the image maps and imports them that way.</div><br />c+ is exactly how level backgrounds in <em>Haunted: Halloween '85</em> and <em>The Curse of Possum Hollow</em> are made. But compared to most NES games, those games prioritize hiding the grid over things like storage efficiency and destructibility of backgrounds.<br /><br />In any case, unless something is actually private, it's best to keep the replies in the forum so that anyone with something meaningful to contribute can contribute.<br /><br />Is there a reason you want to use existing levels rather than creating your own?

		

